metadata.name: Fl‚ô°‚ô°ded #12
metadata.description:
"Fl‚ô°‚ô°ded" is a browser-based 3D environment made with three.js. Inspired by PFP projects, the environment and 3D objects that surround the character change with each generated mint to create a unique meaning to the character's story.

Standing in a flooded area, the character is surrounded by objects that represent different anxieties and relationships to our world in 2022: rising gas prices, threats of rising sea levels due to climate change, the race for the adoption of renewable energies, and the absurdity of continuing to live through those anxieties in our urban and domestic lives alongside the natural world. The powerup or item floating above her head serves as her chosen item for mechanism of survival, sometimes mental, sometimes physical, sometimes a magical item that aids her escapism, sometimes a practical tool.

The 3D character was generated with AI tools. First the character was generated as a 2D image, then passed over to another AI tool to generate a 3D model from that 2D image. The skybox images, with the exception of the grid, were generated with a text-to-image AI tool, and are currently minted in the Cybertwee ‚ô° 2077 collections minted on tezos and ethereum, and can be found on the following platforms:

‚ô° https://versum.xyz/user/tz1RFy7xFU4jCkg8WD21FRtYg8f1g84PVYXX
‚ô° https://foundation.app/collection/cybertwee2077

Controls:
‚ô° Rotate around the scene by dragging the mouse
‚ô° Scroll up/down for zoom
‚ô° Sky items change position on reload
‚ô° View in fullscreen for best experience
‚ô° Can be displayed on a mobile device / tablet or touchscreen monitor

metadata.name: Flower Arrangement #94
metadata.description:
Flower arrangement made by code.

Possible features:
- Style: Natural, Oval, Triangular, Grassy
- Orientation: Square, Portrait, Landscape
- Palette: White, Cream, Tan, Pink, Green, Blue, Yellow, Orange
- Primary flower: Mix, Gerbera, Gerbera 2, Dahlia, Dahlia 2, Spiky, Unknown
- Primary color: Random, Light, Dark
- Secondary color: Random, Light, Dark
- Vase shape: Cylinder, Tumbler, Round, Curve
- Dish: true, false
- Table: true, false
- Texture: true, false

Live view options:
- Press "s" key: Saves the high resolution image (3300 x 3300 for square, 4200 x 3300 for portrait, 3300 x 4200 for landscape)

Depending on the device you run it on, it may take some time for the drawing to complete.
Best viewed in larger window size.
Made with p5js.

August 2022
ykxotkx

metadata.name: The Living Book #1 #1
metadata.description:
I have been exploring the medium of print for years. Mixing etching, silk-screening, offset, photocopy, risography, drawing and painting to design and craft experimental art books.From the day digital, which had always fascinated me, took over my publishing practice, I always liked to create bridges between these two worlds.

The Living Books is part of this series of hybrid and experimental works where paper and digital resonate.

This issue #1 is made of 64 pages that will be minted by collectors. A book will eventually be printed and the pages will follow the mint order. Each page exists in a cover version (c) and a xerox version (x).

Controls :

‚Ä¢ Click to dive into each frame.
‚Ä¢ Press C to toggle cover mode.
‚Ä¢ Press X to toggle xerox mode.
‚Ä¢ Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

The Living Book #1 by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity

metadata.name: Abstract Life #43
metadata.description:
The concept of organic, obtained from living systems, is said to be an effect that, like a plant and a living being, has grown in a completely dynamic manner in different degrees, and no factor except vital forces has prevented its growth. Organic creation is an example of this type. L√©onard de Vinci believed in nature; he wrote, "Painting is a child of nature" in his opinion, art should be compatible with nature. His public image of creativity was "innovation while maintaining fidelity" to nature. According to Michelangelo, the form the artist gives to the materials is in the artist's mind and the materials themselves. Therefore, the artist is always in a metaphysical struggle with the form and secrets of nature. This is a revelatory process through which the artist discovers the mass of paper already hidden in his mind and the materials. As an architect, I tried to create this work while paying attention to the structuralism of shapes and forms in creation, inspired by the colors in nature and my experience in painting and illustration.

To spread the vibe of my beautiful community, minters will own 50% of royalty on each secondary sale.
Eighteen different color palettes and three different borders are used in this artwork.
Made in p5js
Created August 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi
